    "discriminators": [
     "'Very low fidelity, old 8-bit beeps' — and an 8-bit beep is a SQUARE/PULSE wave, which is measurable three ways: (1) crest_factor collapses toward ~1.4, because a square has no peak-to-RMS headroom, (2) total_harmonic_distortion is huge from the odd-harmonic ladder, (3) band_limit_high_hz is low from the era's converters.",
     "That crest/THD pair is what makes LOFI genuinely signal-separable from every other BEEPS sibling, all of which are clean sines.",
     "Shares the squashed-crest + high-THD signature with DESIGNED-DISTORTION; a clean pitched harmonic ladder (high harmonicity) is the tiebreak."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
