     "An EKG monitor is a metronome at heart rate: onset_periodicity near 1 and onset_rate pinned around 1/second, so beats_per_minute lands in the 50-100 range — the human band. That narrow rate window is the most diagnostic thing here.",
     "BEEPS-TIMER is periodic too but typically faster and/or accelerating toward zero; BEEPS-VEHICLE sits near 1 Hz as well but is recorded outdoors with a noise floor and reverberation.",
